notesStmt.note: This working group discussion takes place among representatives from several European universities. The group has been given a document with a number of issues which they need to discuss and put in a logical order and chronological sequence. These issues concern the administrative side of establishing joint degrees among European universities. The speakers also discuss how academic and administrative aspects are related and in which cases they should be addressed separately. S1 is the chairperson and leads the discussion. S10 only joins the group after a couple of minutes. S1 starts by asking if there are any additional issues the participants would like to add to the ones in the document. After that the speakers start to arrange the issues in a temporal sequence. S1 occasionally takes notes. After about 15 minutes, someone joins the group to take notes, but does not participate in the discussion. S12 only joins the group after 25 minutes.
